gum (A tool for glamorous shell scripts)

Gum provides highly configurable, ready-to-use utilities to help you
write useful shell scripts and dotfiles aliases with just a few lines
of code.

Available commands:
  - choose: Choose an option from a list
  - confirm: Ask for confirmation
  - file: Pick a file from a folder
  - filter: Filter items from a list
  - format: Format text (markdown, code, template, emoji)
  - input: Prompt for text input
  - join: Join text vertically or horizontally
  - pager: Scroll through text
  - spin: Display spinner while running a command
  - style: Apply styling to text
  - table: Render a table
  - write: Prompt for multi-line text

This package uses pre-built binaries and is only available for x86_64.
